The paper discusses multi-agent planning, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) that deals with the coordination of multiple agents to achieve a common goal. The paper also mentions partial-order planning, which is a subfield of planning (cs.PL) that deals with the generation of plans that allow for flexibility in the ordering of actions. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of cooperative refinement planning, which is a subfield of multi-agent systems (cs.MA) that deals with the coordination of multiple agents to refine their plans. The paper also mentions the use of machine learning (cs.LG) to improve the performance of the system. Finally, the paper discusses the use of distributed constraint satisfaction problems (CSPs), which is a subfield of distributed computing (cs.DC) that deals with the coordination of multiple agents to solve constraint satisfaction problems.
